/locations/LOC123/booleanattributestest?sourceSystem=web&store=NYC	LOC123 (plus attributes)	false (targets ignore attributes)	✅ Blocked	400
/locations/ANY/booleantest with empty context (not possible from these endpoints)	N/A	–	❌ Skipped	200 (because ldCtx.IsDefined() is false, flag check bypassed)
Note: The two public endpoints always build a defined context, so the bypass never occurs in normal use. It’s a safety fallback.

🧰 Third‑Party API Calls & Mock Usage
LaunchDarkly API: Never called because offline: true. The SDK reads flags.json locally.

Redis: Not used because offline mode takes precedence. If offline were false and redis.enabled: true, the LaunchDarkly client would use Redis as a persistent data store (to share flag data across instances).

Mock API: The only HTTP call made by the app is the internal self‑call from WebClient to MockTargetAPI (same process). This simulates calling a downstream service. No external third‑party service is invoked.

🛡️ Resilience Features (WebClient)
The WebClient (defined in client.go) wraps every DoGet call with:

Retries (exponential backoff)
Enabled by config (retry.enabled: true)

Max attempts = 3

Initial delay = 1000 ms, multiplier = 2.0, max delay = 5000 ms

Retries only on errors (transport errors or HTTP status ≥400)

Circuit Breaker (via gobreaker)
Enabled by config (circuitBreaker.enabled: true)

Failure rate threshold = 50%

